AUDIO: 'couple of things before we get to the seedance 2.0 part. One thing is right now, if I was to hit edit video, remember last time when you saw it automatically synced the video here. This time it\'s not happening. That\'s'

[04:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'because this video on your timeline has to be of less than 30 seconds duration. Right now, this is 42 seconds long. So, the way around it is simply just to trim it till it becomes less than 30 seconds, and now it will reflect here.'

[05:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And that\'s it. You really don\'t have to do anything else. You can select different models, but most of the times it\'s just best to use seedance 2.0 because it\'s going to give you the most consistent results, and we can just'

[05:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'paste in the prompt that we got from Chat GPT. And of course, we can select the duration. Now, it\'s up to you. If your video maximum is 15 seconds in one go in seedance. Now, if your video is longer'

[05:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'than that, then of course, the whole video is not going to get edited. Only the first 15 seconds will get edited. Also, there\'s another important thing to keep in mind, which is that it will always edit the video right from start.'

[05:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, I can\'t do the other way around that I can\'t trim the starting of the video and then hope that it\'ll start from here. No, if you want to start from somewhere else, then you will actually have to trim the video first, export it,'

[06:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and then bring it into Premiere Pro. The point here is whatever is there on the timeline originally when you import it, it will always start from there. Trimming here on the timeline won\'t help that. So, now that you know these'

